To further confirm the detailed localization and the protein 
levels of GLP-1R in the hippocampus, we performed 
immunofluorescence analysis on three areas within the 
hippocampus. In the CA1 region, GLP-1R was highly 
expressed on the pyramidal neuron and somewhat expressed 
on the non-pyramidal cells around the pyramidal layer. The 
GLP-1R immunoreactivity in the CA1 region of the aged mice 
remained at normal levels compared with the young mice 
(Pyramidal neurons: Fig. 5A and 6A, young: 88.1 ± 3.5 
GLP-1R-positive cells per 100 nuclei; aged: 89.1 ± 3.1 
